n \\\"javac\\\" and handle any missing identifiers appropriately. I want to avoid repeating deterministic entries.\\n\\nIt's important to note that if I don’t use a component container, the private compilers map must be initialized to prevent a NullPointerException, but I really prefer to stick with the container approach.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating risks and container setup**\\n\\nI'm considering risks with the old Plexus container and its lifecycle. Running the actual javac might invoke the local JDK, so I want to avoid external processes if I can just retrieve the component. There could be reflection or resource issues from the Plexus components.xml when using native-image. I need to check the dependency tree since the POM parent includes the provided container by default but not transitively. If the test retrieves just the JavacCompiler object, the container default is necessary. I also want to ensure I output a valid JSON object without markdown.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"org.codehaus.plexus:plexus-compiler-manager:2.8.4 is a Plexus component whose main implementation extends a class from the artifact's provided Plexus container dependency; without that extra dependency, loading DefaultCompilerManager fails at runtime. Meaningful happy-path coverage also needs at least one Compiler component implementation registered with the Plexus container.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.codehaus.plexus:plexus-container-default:1.0-alpha-9-stable-1\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"The manager implementation extends org.codehaus.plexus.logging.AbstractLogEnabled from the provided Plexus container dependency; the resolved compile/runtime dependency set does not include it, causing NoClassDefFoundError when DefaultCompilerManager is loaded.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.codehaus.plexus:plexus-compiler-javac:2.8.4\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"The manager's normal role is to retrieve Compiler components by role hint; a concrete compiler component such as the javac implementation is needed for a successful getCompiler(\\\"javac\\\") path instead of only the missing-compiler exception path.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Use a Plexus container for normal usage coverage: create DefaultPlexusContainer, call initialize() and start() before lookup, then dispose() afterward. Cover both successful lookup of a registered compiler role hint such as \\\"javac\\\" and NoSuchCompilerException for an unknown role hint. Avoid tests that only instantiate DefaultCompilerManager directly unless they explicitly initialize its compiler map.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The Plexus container version is old and requires explicit lifecycle calls; omitting initialize()/start() can produce container-internal NullPointerException rather than exercising the library.\",\n    \"Running an actual javac compile is not necessary for manager coverage and may introduce avoidable environment sensitivity; retrieving the component is sufficient for the manager happy path.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_07a981e67a5b381f016a41746f80908190b4fcef9f6f306f52\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 803, "output": 1344, "cacheRead": 22528, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 24675, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782674527394, "responseId": "resp_07a981e67a5b381f016a41745fda6c81909b9eee1a8e516f10"}, "toolResults": []}
